wikipedia_page.main: Frederick James Wilcox (26 December 1882 – 5 April 1959) was an English professional footballer who made 184 appearances in the Football League, most of which were in the First Division, with Small Heath / Birmingham (renamed during his first spell at the club) and Middlesbrough.

response: Twenty-three players made at least one appearance in nationally organised first-team competition, and there were twelve different goalscorers. Forward Charlie Athersmith played in 37 matches over the 38-match season. Billy Jones and Freddie Wilcox were joint leading scorers with eight goals, all of which came in the league.
